sentence: The following companies are expected to report earnings prior to market open on 07/30/2015.
Visit our Earnings Calendar for a full list of expected earnings releases.
Procter & Gamble Company ( PG ) is reporting for the quarter ending June 30, 2015.
The cleaning company's consensus earnings per share forecast from the 12 analysts that follow the stock is $0.94.
This value represents a 1.05% decrease compared to the same quarter last year.
PG missed the consensus earnings per share in the 3rd calendar quarter of 2014 by -0.93%.

Zacks Investment Research reports that the 2015 Price to Earnings ratio for PG is 20.21 vs. an industry ratio of 20.00, implying that they will have a higher earnings growth than their competitors in the same industry.
